This paper is about object detection using ConvNet detection systems, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on learning qualitatively interpretable models, which involves using machine learning techniques to generate explanations for the decisions made by the model, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves using a directed acyclic AND-OR Graph (AOG) to explore and unfold the space of latent part configurations of RoIs, which is a machine learning technique that falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to generate extractive rationales, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves end-to-end training of the AOG and ConvNet, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE).
